%% Data Flow Diagram: TrustyAI Garak Llama Stack Provider
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as User/Client
    participant LLS as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant GarakProv as Garak Remote Provider
    participant KFP as KFP API (DSPA)<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ValPod as KFP: validate
    participant TaxPod as KFP: resolve_taxonomy
    participant SDGPod as KFP: sdg_generate
    participant PrepPod as KFP: prepare_prompts
    participant ScanPod as KFP: garak_scan
    participant ParsePod as KFP: parse_results
    participant FilesAPI as Llama Stack Files API<br/>8321/TCP
    participant vLLM as vLLM / Target LLM<br/>443/TCP

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 1: Remote Garak Scan via KFP

    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/alpha/eval/run_eval<br/>Bearer Token
    LLS->>GarakProv: Dispatch to Garak provider
    GarakProv->>KFP: Submit 6-step pipeline<br/>SA Token, TLS 1.2+

    KFP->>ValPod: Step 1: validate
    ValPod->>LLS: Validate config<br/>8321/TCP

    KFP->>TaxPod: Step 2: resolve_taxonomy
    TaxPod->>FilesAPI: Fetch taxonomy data<br/>8321/TCP

    KFP->>SDGPod: Step 3: sdg_generate
    SDGPod->>SDGPod: Generate adversarial prompts

    KFP->>PrepPod: Step 4: prepare_prompts
    PrepPod->>PrepPod: Prepare Garak config

    KFP->>ScanPod: Step 5: garak_scan
    ScanPod->>vLLM: Probe LLM vulnerabilities<br/>OpenAI API, API Token
    vLLM-->>ScanPod: Chat completions
    ScanPod->>FilesAPI: Upload scan artifacts<br/>JSONL, AVID mappings

    KFP->>ParsePod: Step 6: parse_results
    ParsePod->>FilesAPI: Upload HTML report + TBSA score

    GarakProv->>KFP: Poll pipeline status<br/>SA Token, TLS 1.2+
    KFP-->>GarakProv: Pipeline complete
    GarakProv-->>LLS: Scan results ready

    Client->>LLS: GET /v1/alpha/eval/jobs/status<br/>Bearer Token
    LLS-->>Client: Status: completed

    Client->>LLS: GET /v1/alpha/eval/jobs/retrieve<br/>Bearer Token
    LLS-->>Client: Scan results (TBSA score, reports)

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 2: Inline Garak Scan (Local)

    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/alpha/eval/run_eval<br/>Bearer Token (inline mode)
    LLS->>LLS: Spawn Garak subprocess
    LLS->>vLLM: Probe LLM (via Llama Stack)<br/>8321/TCP internal
    vLLM-->>LLS: Chat completions
    LLS->>LLS: Parse results, upload to Files API
    LLS-->>Client: Scan complete

    Note over Client,vLLM: Flow 3: Shield-Augmented Scan

    Client->>LLS: POST /v1/alpha/eval/run_eval<br/>(with shields enabled)
    LLS->>LLS: SimpleShieldOrchestrator
    LLS->>LLS: Safety API: input shields check
    LLS->>vLLM: LLM inference
    vLLM-->>LLS: Response
    LLS->>LLS: Safety API: output shields check
    LLS-->>Client: Results with shield annotations
